The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                            The City Diary
                Bishnu Jana, 35, was critically injured after the cycle he was riding was hit by a Howrah-bound minibus at the NSC Bose Road-DP Sashmal Road crossing on Friday afternoon. He was taken to MR Bangur Hospital, where he will be kept under observation for 48 hours. The driver fled the spot. Local residents blocked the crossing, demanding action against rash driving. The bus has been impounded.     The pilot of a Guwahati-bound flight of Air India refused to take on board a 75-year-old passenger who fell ill at Calcutta airport on Friday morning. Abdul Mannan, a resident of Karimganj, in Assam, arrived at Calcutta airport on the airlines Haj flight from Jeddah. Mannan was taken to the medical observation room of the airport, where his condition became stable, officials said.     Air Indias Boeing 747 on the London-Calcutta-Dhaka route entered a wrong parking bay after landing at Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport on Friday afternoon. A pilot jeep pulled out the aircraft, with 157 passengers. It left for Dhaka around 3pm.    Calcutta police will kick off its first Traffic Safety Week of the year on January 7.    IT major Cognizant has tied up with Singapore-based linguistic service provider Nihongo Bashi to offer training in Japanisation skills to some of its recruits. The first batch of the course  which will cover Japanese language, business and management  comprises 25 third-year students from an engineering college.                                                                                                                                                                   
